# Add Electronic Invoice Fields to Order Model

## Goal Description
The goal is to support ECPay Electronic Invoice integration by storing necessary invoice parameters in the [Order](file:///c:/coding/template/backend/app/models/order.py#214-363) model. This allows the application to capture user preferences (Carrier Type, Donation, etc.) during order creation and pass them to ECPay.

## User Review Required
> [!IMPORTANT]
> This change involves modifying the database schema. While SQLAlchemy models will be updated, **you (the user) are responsible for running the actual database migration SQL** (provided in [plans/綠界測試.md](file:///c:/coding/template/plans/%E7%B6%A0%E7%95%8C%E6%B8%AC%E8%A9%A6.md)) to apply these changes to your database. This plan only updates the Python code to match the new schema.

## Proposed Changes

### Backend

#### [MODIFY] [order.py](file:///c:/coding/template/backend/app/models/order.py)
- Update [Order](file:///c:/coding/template/backend/app/models/order.py#214-363) class (and potentially [OrderBase](file:///c:/coding/template/backend/app/models/order.py#124-167) or [OrderUpdate](file:///c:/coding/template/backend/app/models/order.py#177-197)) to include the following new fields:
    - `invoice_type` (String): e.g., '2' (Personal) or '3' (Company)
    - `carrier_type` (String): e.g., '3' (Mobile Barcode)
    - `carrier_num` (String): The actual barcode or carrier ID
    - `donation` (String/Char): '1' (Yes) or '0' (No)
    - `love_code` (String): Donation code
    - `print_mark` (String/Char): '0' or '1'

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- None planned for this schema change as no test database is active.

### Manual Verification
1.  **Code Review**: Verify [backend/app/models/order.py](file:///c:/coding/template/backend/app/models/order.py) has the new fields defined.
2.  **Logic Check**: Ensure the new fields map to the SQL provided in [plans/綠界測試.md](file:///c:/coding/template/plans/%E7%B6%A0%E7%95%8C%E6%B8%AC%E8%A9%A6.md).
